      "content": "The escrow agent will typically hold the funds until the deal is finalized or the inspection issue is resolved. If the inspection reveals a major issue that can't be resolved, the escrow agent will usually return the earnest money deposit to you, minus any fees or penalties that may be applicable. This is often referred to as a \"release of escrow\" or \"withdrawal of escrow.\" It's a relatively straightforward process, but it's always a good idea to review your escrow agreement to understand the specific terms and any potential penalties for early withdrawal.",
